message.content:
We note that the “initial” transactions (those with id “Initial20231231001”) show openings for cash, bank and fixed assets – none of which are current liabilities. (They are assets or investments.) In our list the only transactions that generate an “obligation” (that is, a liability) are purchase‐transactions that remain unpaid. (Expenses that have already been paid or transfers among bank and cash do not create a liability; and “interest receivable” entries—although not “paid” yet—represent an asset.)

Looking at all the purchase transactions (ignoring the initial ones):

• Purchase20231231001 – “Purchase” for 340,000.0 – is paid.
• Purchase20231231002 – 1,900,000.0 – paid.
• Purchase20231231003 – 600,000.0 – paid.
• Purchase20231231004 – 260,000.0 – paid.
• Purchase20231231005 – 460,000.0 – its payment/receipt_status is “Unpaid” and the payment method is “Account Payable” so it creates a liability.
• Purchase20231231006 – 450,000.0 – paid.
• Purchase20231231007 – 850,000.0 – paid.
• Purchase20231231008 – 800,000.0 – its status is “Unpaid” (and payment method is “Account Payable”), so it creates a liability.
• Purchase20231231009 – 800,000.0 – paid.
• Purchase20231231010 – 1,500,000.0 – paid.
• Purchase20231231011 – 1,100,000.0 – paid.
• Purchase20231231012 – 60,000.0 – paid.

Thus – the only obligations (current liabilities) arising from purchases are from:
  460,000.0 + 800,000.0 = 1,260,000.0

Other items (expenses, transfers, depreciation, interest “receivables”, and fixed asset purchases) affect the income statement, asset side and accumulated depreciation but do not create current liabilities.

Therefore, at the balance‐sheet date the “current liabilities” are zero in the opening (initial) balance (since no liability was “opened” on 2023‑12‑31) and as a result of the later “unpaid” purchasing transactions the current liabilities “end” value is 1,260,000.00.

Thus the solution in the required json format is:

------------------------------------------------

{"solution": {'Total Current Liabilities Initial Value': '0.00', 'Total Current Liabilities End Value': '1260000.00'} }
